Effective Date: 05/09/2025

1. Introduction

This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and protect your personal data when you interact with the mayFLOW Discord bot ("the Bot"). By using the Bot, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy.

2. Data We Collect

When you use mayFLOW, we may collect the following types of data:

User Data: This includes information like your Discord user ID, username, and any other data you provide when interacting with the bot.

Server Data: Information about the Discord server (e.g., server ID, server name, roles, etc.) may be collected to provide functionalities such as role-based commands, server authorization, and moderation.

Usage Data: This includes logs of how you interact with the bot, such as commands used, frequency of usage, and any errors that occur.

3. How We Use Your Data

We use the collected data to:

Provide and improve the features and functionality of the mayFLOW bot.

Ensure the bot operates effectively and troubleshoot issues.

Respond to support requests and inquiries.

Prevent abuse, spam, and other malicious activities.

Personalize your experience with the bot based on your interactions and preferences.

4. Data Storage

Your data is stored on secure servers. We take reasonable measures to protect your data from unauthorized access, alteration, or destruction. However, no method of transmission over the internet or method of electronic storage is 100% secure, so we cannot guarantee absolute security.

5. Data Sharing and Disclosure

We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal information. However, we may share your data in the following circumstances:

With your consent: If you have given explicit permission, we may share your information with third parties.

Legal Requirements: We may disclose your information if required by law or in response to valid legal requests, such as subpoenas or court orders.

Service Providers: We may employ third-party companies and individuals to assist with the operation of the Bot. These service providers have access to your data only to perform specific tasks on our behalf and are obligated not to disclose or use it for other purposes.

6. Data Retention

We retain your data only as long as necessary to provide our services and for legal or operational purposes. If you wish to request the deletion of your data, please contact us using the contact details provided below.

7. Your Rights

As a user, you have the right to:

Access: You may request information about the data we hold about you.

Correction: You may request corrections to any inaccurate or incomplete data we hold.

Deletion: You may request the deletion of your data, subject to any legal obligations or other necessary data retention requirements.

To exercise these rights, please contact us using the contact details provided below.

8. Children's Privacy

mayFLOW is not intended for use by children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If we become aware that a child under 13 has provided us with personal data, we will take steps to delete such information from our records.

9. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we make changes, we will update the "Effective Date" at the top of this page. We encourage you to review this policy periodically to stay informed about how we are protecting your data.

10. Contact Us

If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or wish to exercise your rights regarding your data, please contact me on Discord @vaporized
